# Automation & n8n Rules

## n8n instance

- URL: https://n8n.franchisetech.ro
- Connected via n8n-mcp in .cursor/mcp.json
- Use MCP to CREATE workflows — do not write raw JSON workflow files manually

## Webhook convention

All n8n webhooks that Next.js calls must:

- Accept POST with JSON body
- Include { email, userId, businessName } at minimum
- Be documented in a comment above the fetch() call in the Next.js code

## Priority workflows to build (in order)

1. Trial Conversion Alert (z_report_viewed → check Stripe → Telegram if no subscription)
2. Cold email pipeline (CSV → dedup Supabase → Zoho send → log result)
3. Stripe churn warning (past_due → Loops payment issue sequence → Telegram)
4. Weekly metrics digest (Monday 8am → Supabase + Stripe query → email summary)
5. Partner lead routing (form submit → Supabase insert → Loops partner sequence → Telegram)

## Credential storage

All credentials in n8n must use n8n Credential nodes — never hardcoded in workflow nodes.
Supabase: use service role key stored as n8n HTTP Header Auth credential.
Telegram: use n8n Telegram credential node.
Stripe: use n8n Stripe credential node.
Loops: use n8n HTTP Request node with Authorization header from credential.
